{{Refimprove|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox book | name = The Billion-Dollar Molecule | image = The Billion Dollar Molecule-large.jpg | image_size = 200 | caption = Paperback edition | author = Barry Werth | country = United States | language = English | subject = [[Biotechnology]] | genre = [[Non-fiction]] | publisher = [[Simon & Schuster]] | release_date = February 16, 1994 | pages = 448 pp. <small>(hardcover)</small> | isbn = 0-671-51057-6 }} '''''The Billion-Dollar Molecule''''' is a book<ref name="Werth">{{citation |title=The Billion-Dollar Molecule: The Quest for the Perfect Drug |author=Barry Werth |pages=448 |publisher= Simon & Schuster |date=February 16, 1994 |isbn=0671510576}}</ref> by journalist [[Barry Werth]] about the founding and early research efforts of the American [[biotechnology]] company [[Vertex Pharmaceuticals]], which was founded in 1989 by [[Joshua Boger]] and was among the first biotechnology companies to adopt an explicit strategy of [[rational drug design]] as opposed to techniques based on [[combinatorial chemistry]].
This book is notable as an inside look at a biotechnology company, and the stresses and marketing pressures on funding research into drug design. This book is a mixture of finance and technology.
In February, 2014, Barry Werth published a follow-on book, ''The Antidote'',<ref name="Antidote_2014">{{cite book |title=The Antidote Inside the World of New Pharma |author=Barry Werth |url=http://books.simonandschuster.com/Antidote/Barry-Werth/9781451655667 |publisher=Simon & Schuster |pages= 448 | isbn= 9781451655674 | date=December 2014 |accessdate=July 19, 2015}}</ref> that looks at Vertex 20 years later after his original effort.<ref>http://www.barrywerth.com retrieved 2014-01-01</ref>
